@page
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "On the Topic of AI - Destroyere1107's Home Page";
    ViewData["ActiveNav"] = "nav-ai-topic";
}

<div id="content">
    <h2>On the Topic of AI</h2>
    <p>
        Artificial intelligence (in this case, generative AI in particular)
        is everywhere these days. Emphasis on 'Everywhere'. I mean,
        seriously. Look at this image below that I haven't added yet.
    </p>

    <h3>The Truth</h3>
    <p>
        AI is here to stay. Even after the bubble pops, we have invested so
        much money into it that it would be a fool's errand to try to get
        rid of it. It's a wonderful technology with amazing applications -
        so long as you use it right...
    </p>

    <h3>The Good</h3>
    <p>
        AI is really good at doing menial tasks. I personally used it to
        make some of the HTML and CSS for this page. It's great for getting
        the easy and repetitive stuff done so that I can focus on harder
        things.
    </p>

    <h3>The Bad</h3>
    <p>
        Despite all the good it can do, we as a civilization seem intent on
        using it for all the wrong reasons. Corpos seem to believe that
        GenAI is able to completely replace a human being in any context.
        Spoiler alert: it can't. It's a tool. A very powerful tool, but a
        tool nonetheless. A tool that can easily hallucinate, write awful
        code, make weird things. When used
        <i>properly</i> (under supervision by a skiled human) it's great.
        But alas, technology exists only as a way to extract more value from
        the economy...
    </p>

    <h3>My Take</h3>
    <p>
        Any John Q. Public can use GenAI to make something. Hell, that's
        what I did with this webpage. But in order to make something
        <i>good</i>, nothing can beat the indomitable human spirit.
    </p>
    <p>Ultimately:</p>
    <p>
        <b>If in doubt about using AI, ask yourself: given time and
            resources, could you do it without AI?</b>
    </p>
    <p>
        <b>If that answer is no, then don't bother with it. Go learn. Read
            the documentation. Change until that answer is yes, so that you
            can change AI work to meet human standards.</b>
    </p>

    <p class="shout">
        <b>Remember: an LLM is only as poweful as the human directing it.</b>
    </p>
    <p>An extra note: I will <b>never</b> use AI to generate content, meaning the text or images you see on this site, as noted in the footer. I have only and will only use it to assist me in coding and structure.</p>

